body:
Bank Robbery

The avengers were doing daily patrol around the city when suddenly Clint noticed something.

“Robbery at 11 o'clock. I’ve placed trackers on all five of them.” Clint said standing on top of a building.

“Where?” Cap asked riding a motorcycle with Black Widow.

“Down the street to your left.” Hawkeye replied.

“Let’s go!” Iron Man said as he flew through the sky around buildings and then caught up to Steve and Nat.


“HURRY UP YOU MORON!” One of the bank robbers yelled at the other five.

“HEY!” Cap yelled waking into the bank.

“That money isn’t for stealing boys!” Black Widow said pointing a gun at them.

“Shit! IT’S THE AVENGERS!” One of them said and then pushed a button which caused a loud bang and the building to collapse.

“Get down!” Cap said and then held his sheild over him and Nat to protect them when suddenly the building stopped falling.

A red aura outlined the falling chunks of the banks roof.

The peices flew to one side of the bank causing them to shatter into a bunch of pieces. The sunlight blinded Steve and Nat causing them to put one hand in front of them while still staying alert.

The sun painted a figure of a young woman who stood there with red energy orbs that made her hand look like small red clouds.

Captain America and Black Widow approached the figure to reveal Wanda, Scarlet Witch.

“Are you two alright?” She asked.

“Yes, thank you.” Nat replied.

“Yeah, thanks. Now where’d they go-” Cap was cut off by gun shots and screaming.

“Up ahead!” Tony said as he scanned the perimeter.

“They have civilians at gun point!” Tony said when suddenly a red figure swung through the sky.

“What the?” One of the robbers yelled.


When Nat, Steve, Wanda, and Tony arrived at the scene, one of the robbers were webbed to the wall.

“Hey Mr. Stark.” It was Spider-Man, Peter Parker.

“Good job, kid. Now there’s four more.” Tony said.

“Let’s go!” Wanda said and used her energy to shoot herself in the air.


Thirty minutes later, after the job was done, the heros headed back to the tower.

“Wait a second, what is that?” Clint said pointing at Spider-Man, who he hadn’t met yet.

Hawkeye thought that he was some sort of villain as he swung through the clouds directly at Nat and the others.

“Oh no you don’t!” He said pointing his arrow at him following his every move.

When Peter got close to the Avengers, Hawkeye fired.

The arrow hit Peter’s shoulder and he fell to the ground in pain.

“Got you.” Hawkeye said as Peter was falling to his death.

“WAIT! SPIDER-MAN!” Wanda alerted the others as she pointed at a falling Peter. She shot herself in the air with Tony and used her magic to slow down his fall while Tony caught him.

He brought him down to the ground safely.

“OH MY GOD! NO!” Nat said as she took him from Tony and held him close to her chest.

blog.title: Hawaii Five-O, Supernatural, And More.
blog.description: I love Supernatural and Hawaii Five-O. I love Jack Maynard, Dean Winchester, Chris Hemsworth but most of all the one and only Jensen Ackles and Chris Evans. Masterlist:

summary: Every time I go and try to read a Chris or Steve writing it just keeps giving me other people that I don’t want to read. 😪
